---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import StructuredData from '../../components/StructuredData.astro';

const comparisonData = {
  date: 'January 20, 2025',
  tool1: {
    name: 'Relume',
    slug: '/reviews/relume-ai'
  },
  tool2: {
    name: 'Figma',
    slug: 'https://www.figma.com'
  }
};

const quickVerdict = {
    relume: 'Best for Webflow sitemap and wireframe generation',
    figma: 'Best for collaborative design and prototyping',
    winner: 'Relume for Webflow sites, Figma for design teams'
};

---

<Layout title="Relume vs Figma: Webflow Planning vs Design Tool">

  <StructuredData
    type="WebPage"
    data={{
      name: 'Relume vs Figma: Webflow Planning vs Design Tool',
      description: 'Relume generates Webflow sitemaps and wireframes with AI. Figma is the collaborative design tool for UI/UX. One plans Webflow sites, one designs everything.',
      url: 'https://aiwebsitebuilders.com/comparisons/relume-vs-figma'
    }}
  />

  <section class="relative overflow-hidden bg-[#FFF8F0]">
    <div class="absolute top-0 right-0 w-[45%] h-full opacity-[0.04]" style="background-image: repeating-linear-gradient(45deg, #F5521A 0px, #F5521A 1px, transparent 1px, transparent 12px);"></div>
    <div class="absolute bottom-0 left-0 w-32 h-32 bg-[#F5521A]/5 rounded-tr-[100px]"></div>

    <div class="container mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 max-w-7xl relative">
      <div class="py-12 md:py-16 lg:py-20">
        <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto space-y-6">

          <div class="inline-flex items-center gap-3 px-4 py-3 bg-white border-[3px] border-[#F5521A] shadow-[0_4px_0_0_rgba(245,82,26,0.3)]">
            <div class="flex gap-2">
              <span class="w-2 h-2 bg-[#F5521A] rotate-45"></span>
              <span class="w-2 h-2 bg-[#F5521A] rotate-45" style="animation-delay: 0.15s"></span>
              <span class="w-2 h-2 bg-[#F5521A] rotate-45" style="animation-delay: 0.3s"></span>
            </div>
            <span class="text-xs font-black tracking-widest text-gray-800" style="font-family: 'Space Mono', monospace;">
              {comparisonData.date} · COMPARISON
            </span>
          </div>

          <h1 class="text-4xl sm:text-5xl md:text-6xl lg:text-7xl font-black leading-[0.9] tracking-tight text-gray-900">
            <span class="block">Relume vs Figma:</span>
            <span class="block text-[#F5521A] mt-2">Planning vs Design</span>
          </h1>

          <div class="max-w-2xl">
            <p class="text-lg sm:text-xl text-gray-800/95 font-medium leading-relaxed">
              Relume generates Webflow sitemaps and wireframes with AI. Figma is the industry-standard collaborative design tool. One helps plan Webflow sites, one designs everything.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <main class="max-w-3xl mx-auto">
    <article class="px-6 py-16 lg:py-24">
      <div class="prose prose-lg max-w-none">
        <div class="bg-[#F5521A]/5 border-l-4 border-[#F5521A] p-6 my-8">
          <p class="text-gray-900">
            <strong>The one-sentence answer:</strong><br />
            Use Relume if you are building Webflow sites and want AI planning.<br />
            Use Figma if you need a collaborative design tool for any platform.<br /><br />
            Relume wins for Webflow workflow. Figma wins for design collaboration.
          </p>
        </div>

        <h2 class="text-2xl md:text-3xl font-black text-gray-900 mt-12 mb-6 flex items-center gap-3">
          <div class="w-1 h-8 bg-[#F5521A]"></div>They are not competitors
        </h2>
        <p class="text-gray-600 leading-relaxed mb-6">
          Relume and Figma serve different purposes. Relume plans Webflow sites—sitemaps, wireframes, component libraries that export to Webflow. Figma designs anything—UI, UX, prototypes, handoffs for any platform.
        </p>
        <p class="text-gray-600 leading-relaxed mb-6">
          <strong>Use them together:</strong> Plan your Webflow site with Relume, export to Webflow, then use Figma for custom illustrations and graphics.
        </p>

        <div class="my-8 p-6 bg-gray-100 border-[3px] border-gray-300">
          <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6 text-sm">
            <div>
              <div class="text-gray-600 mb-2">Relume:</div>
              <p class="text-gray-900">{quickVerdict.relume}</p>
            </div>
            <div>
              <div class="text-gray-600 mb-2">Figma:</div>
              <p class="text-gray-900">{quickVerdict.figma}</p>
            </div>
          </div>
          <p class="text-xs text-gray-600 mt-4 pt-4 border-t border-gray-300">
            <strong>Verdict:</strong> {quickVerdict.winner}
          </p>
        </div>

        <h2 class="text-2xl md:text-3xl font-black text-gray-900 mt-12 mb-6 flex items-center gap-3">
          <div class="w-1 h-8 bg-[#F5521A]"></div>Quick comparison
        </h2>
        <div class="overflow-x-auto my-8">
          <table class="w-full text-left border-collapse">
            <thead>
              <tr class="border-b border-gray-300">
                <th class="py-3 px-4 text-gray-600 font-medium">Metric</th>
                <th class="py-3 px-4 text-gray-900 font-black">Relume</th>
                <th class="py-3 px-4 text-gray-900 font-black">Figma</th>
                <th class="py-3 px-4 text-gray-600 font-medium">Winner</th>
              </tr>
            </thead>
            <tbody>
              <tr class="border-b border-gray-300">
                <td class="py-3 px-4 text-gray-600">Primary use</td>
                <td class="py-3 px-4 text-gray-900">Webflow planning</td>
                <td class="py-3 px-4 text-gray-900">General design</td>
                <td class="py-3 px-4 text-gray-500 font-medium">Different</td>
              </tr>
              <tr class="border-b border-gray-300">
                <td class="py-3 px-4 text-gray-600">Webflow export</td>
                <td class="py-3 px-4 text-gray-900">Native, seamless</td>
                <td class="py-3 px-4 text-gray-900">Plugin required</td>
                <td class="py-3 px-4 text-green-600 font-medium">Relume</td>
              </tr>
              <tr class="border-b border-gray-300">
                <td class="py-3 px-4 text-gray-600">Sitemap generation</td>
                <td class="py-3 px-4 text-gray-900">AI-powered</td>
                <td class="py-3 px-4 text-gray-900">Manual</td>
                <td class="py-3 px-4 text-green-600 font-medium">Relume</td>
              </tr>
              <tr class="border-b border-gray-300">
                <td class="py-3 px-4 text-gray-600">Real-time collaboration</td>
                <td class="py-3 px-4 text-gray-900">Limited</td>
                <td class="py-3 px-4 text-gray-900">Excellent</td>
                <td class="py-3 px-4 text-green-600 font-medium">Figma</td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td class="py-3 px-4 text-gray-600">Cost</td>
                <td class="py-3 px-4 text-gray-900">Free tier available</td>
                <td class="py-3 px-4 text-gray-900">Free tier available</td>
                <td class="py-3 px-4 text-gray-500 font-medium">Tie</td>
              </tr>
            </tbody>
          </table>
        </div>

        <h2 class="text-2xl md:text-3xl font-black text-gray-900 mt-12 mb-6 flex items-center gap-3">
          <div class="w-1 h-8 bg-[#F5521A]"></div>Where Relume wins
        </h2>

        <h3 class="text-xl font-black text-gray-900 mt-8 mb-4">Webflow export</h3>
        <p class="text-gray-600 leading-relaxed mb-6">
          Copy and paste into Webflow. Sitemaps, wireframes, components—all export perfectly. Figma requires a plugin to export to Webflow, and it is not as seamless.
        </p>

        <h3 class="text-xl font-black text-gray-900 mt-8 mb-4">AI sitemap generation</h3>
        <p class="text-gray-600 leading-relaxed mb-6">
          Describe your site, Relume generates a complete sitemap with pages and sections. Figma requires manual sitemap creation. If you want AI assistance planning your site structure, Relume wins.
        </p>

        <h3 class="text-xl font-black text-gray-900 mt-8 mb-4">Component library</h3>
        <p class="text-gray-600 leading-relaxed mb-6">
          Relume includes a Webflow component library. Buttons, forms, navigation—all designed to work in Webflow. Figma has components but they are not Webflow-specific.
        </p>

        <h2 class="text-2xl md:text-3xl font-black text-gray-900 mt-12 mb-6 flex items-center gap-3">
          <div class="w-1 h-8 bg-[#F5521A]"></div>Where Figma wins
        </h2>

        <h3 class="text-xl font-black text-gray-900 mt-8 mb-4">Design freedom</h3>
        <p class="text-gray-600 leading-relaxed mb-6">
          Design anything for any platform. Mobile apps, websites, presentations, logos. Relume is focused on Webflow sites. If you need general-purpose design, Figma wins.
        </p>

        <h3 class="text-xl font-black text-gray-900 mt-8 mb-4">Real-time collaboration</h3>
        <p class="text-gray-600 leading-relaxed mb-6">
          Multiple people editing simultaneously. Comments, cursors, version history. Figma is built for teams. Relume has collaboration but it is not Figma-level.
        </p>

        <h3 class="text-xl font-black text-gray-900 mt-8 mb-4">Prototyping</h3>
        <p class="text-gray-600 leading-relaxed mb-6">
          Interactive prototypes with smart animate. Test user flows before building. Figma is the prototyping standard. Relume does not focus on prototyping.
        </p>

        <h2 class="text-2xl md:text-3xl font-black text-gray-900 mt-12 mb-6 flex items-center gap-3">
          <div class="w-1 h-8 bg-[#F5521A]"></div>The ideal workflow
        </h2>
        <p class="text-gray-600 leading-relaxed mb-6">
          <strong>Use both together:</strong> Plan your Webflow site with Relume, export to Webflow for development, then use Figma for custom graphics, illustrations, and non-Webflow designs.
        </p>
        <p class="text-gray-600 leading-relaxed mb-6">
          Relume handles the Webflow-specific planning. Figma handles the broader design work. They are complementary tools, not competitors.
        </p>

        <h2 class="text-2xl md:text-3xl font-black text-gray-900 mt-12 mb-6 flex items-center gap-3">
          <div class="w-1 h-8 bg-[#F5521A]"></div>Bottom line
        </h2>
        <p class="text-gray-600 leading-relaxed mb-6">
          Relume is the Webflow planning tool—AI sitemaps, wireframes, seamless export. Figma is the design standard—collaboration, prototyping, platform-agnostic.<br /><br />
          If you are building a Webflow site, start with Relume. If you need a general design tool for any platform, use Figma. They work best together.
        </p>

        <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-4 my-12">
          <a href={comparisonData.tool1.slug} class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 px-6 py-3 bg-white border-[3px] border-gray-300 text-gray-900 font-medium hover:border-[#F5521A] hover:text-[#F5521A] transition-colors">
            Read Relume review
          </a>
          <a href="/comparisons/relume-vs-framer" class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 px-6 py-3 bg-white border-[3px] border-gray-300 text-gray-900 font-medium hover:border-[#F5521A] hover:text-[#F5521A] transition-colors">
            Compare Relume vs Framer
          </a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </article>
  </main>

</Layout>
